==Rawk 
An awk implementation in ruby

=Example

A simple awk program

$ ls -ltr | awk '
>   BEGIN {print "Starting..."}
>   {print $9, $1}
>   END {print "done"} '

Starting...
 total
spec drwxr-xr-x
lib drwxr-xr-x
bin drwxr-xr-x
README -rw-r--r--
done

This can be written using rawk as

$ ls -ltr | bin/rawk '
>   start {puts "Starting..."}
>   every {|record| puts "#{record.cols[8]} #{record.cols[0]}"}
>   finish {puts "done"}
> '

Starting...
 total
spec drwxr-xr-x
lib drwxr-xr-x
bin drwxr-xr-x
README -rw-r--r--
done
